<plot>An English version of "Rechov Sumsum" (1983) released as a mini-series on PBS and as a video series. Instead of Big Bird, we have a big porcupine named Kippi and a brown grouch named Oofnick who is Oscar's cousin. The show teaches children about the areas throughout Israel and about the Jewish holidays like Chanunakah. The second wave of episodes, aired in 1992, used more of a variety format (except for the Passover episode) while still teaching about Judiesism. Every episode contains a guest appearance, including 3 by Oscar the Grouch.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?490301</url></doc>
